entries.femaleVariant: First place, V! Oh my fuckin' God, we won!
We did it, V. We're finals bound!
Fuck!
Don't stop yet, OK? Move up a bit further.
Need to talk. Somethin' you should know.
OK.
[Sit] Nice view.
Wanted to tell me something?
I mentioned Dean before... my husband, yeah?
And me? Guess you want my help to zero him?
Killing Sampson matters more than taking first. If we have to make a choice…
Bastard won't finish the race alive.
My priority's winning.
Sorry, Claire, but I can't help.
Means a lot to you, this... so yeah, let's bury the bastard.
Thank you. This… it's important. I need it.
Want no part in this, Claire. I'm out, sorry.
That's it? Gonna walk? You sure about that?
If Sampson dies by the rules of the game... all right.
But I won't help you execute the guy. Can't count on that.
That's fair, I can agree to that.
Wow, quite the view.
Sit down for a spell over there, 'kay?
We're finals bound, yeah!
Hell yeah.
Ah, sorry, Claire...
We cocked it up!
Try again next year.
There's always next year.
Gave it our best, can't deny that.
Did our best.
Next year? Ugh... you don't get it.
So what? Not how this was s'posed to be…
Whatever, let's roll outta here. Wanna get home.
Yeah.
What for?
You feel at fault for his death?
What's the connection to our race?
Sayin' you feel at fault for his death?
entries.maleVariant: You sayin' you feel at fault for his death?

entries.femaleVariant: This have something to do with our race?
Me, at fault? Why would you think that?
Sort of. Thing is... Dean was murdered.
Tell me about this corpo Sampson?
He was flatlined by a corpo-ego-weasel – Peter Sampson, exceptional walking rot.
What happened to your husband exactly?
What's the corpo's deal?
Your husband, how'd he die exactly?
Right, so this isn't business as usual. For you, this isn't about winning.
Doesn't really matter. Was only ever another adversary to me. But to Dean…
Dean and Sampson had a history goin' way back.
Somethin' happen 'tween 'em?
Dean never admitted anything, but yeah… yeah, there was some kind of strife.
We'd just powered into the final straight, Sampson peelin' up the tarmac ahead of us.
Was clear we couldn't win, so Dean let up on the chooh…
And then that snake slammed on the brakes. Dean also had to. He lost control…
But… isn't that how this race works?
You don't get it. Road was clear to the finish line! He woulda won. It was premeditated!
That's right. Fuck winning. I want Sampson dead.
And this your best plan for vengeance?
entries.maleVariant: And this is your best plan for vengeance?

entries.femaleVariant: Want my help to kill Sampson?
What if Sampson's not racing this year?
And if Sampson doesn't show for the race, what then?
Pff. He'd never miss a chance to puff out his chest. He'll race.
Circuit champ last year. No way he'll let that go, not try to repeat.
Sorry I lied to you, V.
Yeah. Me and Dean – we liked to come here.
I'm sure. Just not what I signed up for.
I get that. OK, guess I'm done here.
Will ya look for another driver?
I will. But if I can't, I'll go it alone. Goodbye, V.
It's all I can promise. And trust me... revenge don't soothe your soul.
Just makes you a killer, that's all.
entries.maleVariant: It just makes you a killer, that's all.

entries.femaleVariant: Not the way I see it. But fine, till the final, V.
See you for the final?
That's right. Till then, V.
Your driver, yeah.
Mind refreshin' my memory?
Wheel to your heat, right?
Gimme a quick refresher?
Why tell me about him?
Don't see any implants on you.
Mind if I ask why you don't sport any chrome?
entries.maleVariant: Hey, you mind if I ask why you don't sport any chrome?

entries.femaleVariant: Why tell me about Dean? M-meanin', why now…
entries.maleVariant: Why tell me about Dean? Meanin', why now…

entries.femaleVariant: I love machines, V, I do, but I don't ever wanna become one. That weird?
A little, I guess. But it's fine.
He died durin' a race last year. The final.
Not your standard fatality, though.
Congratulations to V and Claire!
Congratulations to Luigi and Margot!
You a hundred percent sure the killing was deliberate? Not your emotions talkin' now?
You sure it was murder?
So there's more to this race.
Something personal to their rally rivalry. When Sampson came first, Dean got hot and bothered.
No, saw them argue till the crack of the starting gun... Gonna kill that bastard.
During the race?
Folks die on the track all the time – won't seem unusual at all.
Another day at the races, in line with the rules.
Sweetest man I ever knew. We were friends before my gender transition.
Brought daffodils to the hospital... To new beginnings, he said…
Were you married long?
Twelve years. Dean used to laugh that for our fifteenth…
Said he'd finally talk me into my first implant. Was prepping some surprise.
Okay, I'll still drive. But only to win.
Yeah, Claire. I'm done.
Fine, I'll drive. With winnin' as my sole objective.
[Stand]
Dean – only person who coulda convinced me to chrome up. But... guess we'll never know if he'da managed, huh?
C'mon, V. We need to talk, I need to.
Hmm... V?
So? Whaddaya say?
Slaughterhouse-bloody means a damn good race! Woohoo!
